{"TopicId":156471,"ForumId":15,"TopicTitle":"One emissive animation.","CreatedByName":"Alcentar","CreatedById":173249,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-15T09:37:47Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Alcentar","CreatedById":173249,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-15T09:37:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello guys, who can tell how to make something work one emissive animations on several nozzles at once on one engine?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"InsaneDruid","CreatedById":137849,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-15T10:28:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf i can remember it correctly then the animation component must sit on the parent part that has the nozzles as children?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alcentar","CreatedById":173249,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-15T10:37:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222956004\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156471\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221487154539\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137849\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022InsaneDruid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, InsaneDruid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf i can remember it correctly then the animation component must sit on the parent part that has the nozzles as children?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat is, create an empty GameData and put the nozzle back? I just tried this option and many more.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"InsaneDruid","CreatedById":137849,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-15T17:55:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, cutting the animation component (like you would delete the mesh renderer component on a collider part) from (one of) the nozzles and putting it to the parent of the nozzles and referencing it there in the cfg.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alcentar","CreatedById":173249,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-16T14:03:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222956004\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156471\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221487154539\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137849\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022InsaneDruid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 15.02.2017 at 1:28 PM, InsaneDruid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you for your advice, I was able to fix it !!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}